
[1]comforter

   COMFORTER, n.

   1. One who administers comfort or consolation; one who strengthens and
   supports the mind in distress or danger.

   I looked for comforters, but found none. Ps. 69.

   Miserable comforters are ye all. Job. 16.

   2. The title of the Holy Spirit, whom the Father will send in my
   name--he shall teach you all things. John 14.
